  "texts": [
    "At this stage, high transverse momentum jets and heavy flavor pair are produced because of the large momentum transfer.",
    "Subsequently, the QGP expands and cools down, entering into the mixed-phase expansion.",
    "The chemical freeze-out point is formed after the inelastic interaction stops, which means that thereafter particle yields and ratios do not change.",
    "After chemical freezeout, the elastic interaction between hadrons and resonance decays [31] change the p T distribution of particles.",
    "The particles finally freeze out of the system after the elastic interaction stops, at the so-called kinetic freeze-out point."
